ider**\\n\\nI wonder if there's a public concrete no-arg NanoTimer provider in the library. It seems like a good idea to check this out. The absence of such a provider might complicate things, but if one exists, it would simplify usage significantly. I'll start by searching through the library documentation or available resources to find the relevant information. Let's see what I can discover about this NanoTimer provider. It could be quite helpful!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dQt39UyOWhXSEOzVags6x09u|fc_05dda201aebe89c50169efe271805881a2b87c5f6b0c95b0cb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"implements NanoTimer|NanoTimer\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/backport-util-concurrent/backport-util-concurrent/3.1/main/extracted -n", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1512, "output": 1049, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31233, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777328734335, "responseId": "resp_05dda201aebe89c50169efe25ecf1c81a2ac24673a98e57cd3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_dQt39UyOWhXSEOzVags6x09u|fc_05dda201aebe89c50169efe271805881a2b87c5f6b0c95b0cb", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/backport-util-concurrent/backport-util-concurrent/3.1/main/extracted/edu/emory/mathcs/backport/java/util/concurrent/helpers/Utils.java:37:    private final static NanoTimer nanoTimer;\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/backport-util-concurrent/backport-util-concurrent/3.1/main/extracted/edu/emory/mathcs/backport/java/util/concurrent/helpers/Utils.java:39:        \"edu.emory.mathcs.backport.java.util.concurrent.NanoTimerProvider\";\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/s